# Custom Theme

```elixir
Mix.install([
  {:mdex, "~> 0.8"},
  {:kino, "~> 0.16"}
])
```

## Example

Below we'll customize an existing theme but any [%Autumn.Theme{}](https://hexdocs.pm/autumn/Autumn.Theme.html) would work, even if built from scratch.

```elixir
theme = Autumn.Theme.get("github_light")

function_call_style =
  %Autumn.Theme.Style{
    fg: "#d1242f",
    bg: "#e4b7be",
    bold: true
  }

new_theme = put_in(
  theme,
  [Access.key!(:highlights), Access.key!("function.call")],
  function_call_style
)
```

